%% Diagram: Payment lifecycle sequence
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant API as Payment API
    participant F as Fraud Engine
    participant P as Processor
    participant N as Card Network
    participant I as Issuer
    participant L as Ledger

    C->>API: POST /payments (Idempotency-Key)
    API->>API: Idempotency check + lock
    API->>F: Score transaction
    F-->>API: allow (risk 25)
    API->>P: Create PaymentIntent
    P->>N: Authorization request
    N->>I: Verify funds + risk
    I-->>N: Approved
    N-->>P: Auth ok (auth code)
    P-->>API: Authorized
    API->>L: Record auth (DR AR / CR hold)
    API-->>C: 201 authorized

    Note over C,L: Later — capture (within network window)

    C->>API: POST /payments/{id}/capture
    API->>P: Capture
    P->>N: Capture
    N-->>P: Captured
    P-->>API: Captured
    API->>L: Record capture (DR hold / CR revenue)
    API-->>C: 200 captured

    Note over C,L: T+1 to T+3 — settlement

    P-->>API: payout.paid webhook
    API->>L: Settlement entry (cash, fees, AR)
